you to jail for that.

506
00:26:02.527 --> 00:26:03.987
You gave Tasha your word.

507
00:26:06.073 --> 00:26:07.699
So that's what this is about.

508
00:26:10.167 --> 00:26:11.960
You coming back into my life.

509
00:26:13.705 --> 00:26:16.041
No. No way.

510
00:26:17.000 --> 00:26:18.502
You know better than that.

511
00:26:19.252 --> 00:26:21.461
I just don't want something
bad happening to the family

512
00:26:21.463 --> 00:26:22.554
because you got scared.

513
00:26:22.557 --> 00:26:23.808
I am scared.

514
00:26:24.558 --> 00:26:26.349
And I got a goddamn right to be.

515
00:26:26.352 --> 00:26:27.854
I know. and it's fucked up.

516
00:26:28.845 --> 00:26:32.013
But I'll tell you this.
Tasha is smart. talk to her.

517
00:26:32.015 --> 00:26:33.649
If we're gonna get out of this thing.

518
00:26:33.652 --> 00:26:35.279
you got to do what she says.

519
00:26:37.395 --> 00:26:40.941
And then. we ain't fucking
with her or Ghost anymore.

520
00:26:58.250 --> 00:27:00.250
Hey. son. I got a question for you.

521
00:27:00.252 --> 00:27:02.001
When you were running with Kanan.

522
00:27:02.003 --> 00:27:04.005
you ever see Dre and Ray Ray together?

523
00:27:04.673 --> 00:27:06.923
Yep. in your friend Breeze's apartment.

524
00:27:06.925 --> 00:27:08.081
where you killed him.

525
00:27:09.302 --> 00:27:10.659
Did Kanan tell you that?

526
00:27:13.640 --> 00:27:15.684
You killed your own friend. Breeze.

527
00:27:16.434 --> 00:27:19.853
For some territory? To
get ahead in the game?

528
00:27:19.855 --> 00:27:21.148
Breeze was a bad dude.

529
00:27:21.773 --> 00:27:23.191
He was gonna get us all killed.

530
00:27:23.942 --> 00:27:26.236
You come here asking
me about Kanan. why?

531
00:27:27.154 --> 00:27:28.862
You want to frame him again?

532
00:27:28.864 --> 00:27:31.199
Tariq. I do what I need
to do to solve problems.

533
00:27:31.950 --> 00:27:35.036
I'm not framing Kanan to solve
this one. I promise you that.

534
00:27:36.371 --> 00:27:39.330
You're going to frame Dre. How though?

535
00:27:39.332 --> 00:27:41.708
He wasn't there. how are you
going to prove he was there?

536
00:27:41.710 --> 00:27:43.308
And then what if that doesn't work?

537
00:27:43.311 --> 00:27:45.484
- Then Mom goes to jail?
- No. if that doesn't work.

538
00:27:45.487 --> 00:27:46.963
then I turn myself in for Ray Ray.

539
00:27:46.965 --> 00:27:48.214
Not your mother. I'm your father.

540
00:27:48.216 --> 00:27:49.674
and your life is my responsibility.

541
00:27:49.676 --> 00:27:51.887
Yeah. right. you'll just
find another way out.

542
00:27:58.602 --> 00:28:00.685
You're my son. all right?

543
00:28:00.687 --> 00:28:03.021
And what that means is I
would do anything for you.

544
00:28:03.023 --> 00:28:04.689
Including sacrificing my life

545
00:28:04.691 --> 00:28:06.941
to give you the future
I think you deserve.

546
00:28:06.943 --> 00:28:09.571
You don't have to
believe it. but it's true.

547
00:28:11.573 --> 00:28:13.776
So you're going to jail. not Ma?

548
00:28:13.779 --> 00:28:16.825
Tariq. no one in this family is
going to jail if I can help it.

549
00:28:16.828 --> 00:28:20.580
but yes. I'll take the rap. not Ma.

550
00:28:34.888 --> 00:28:35.889
Tariq.

551
00:28:36.681 --> 00:28:37.933
We need to talk.

552
00:28:38.850 --> 00:28:41.434
20. 40. 60. 80. 100.

553
00:28:41.437 --> 00:28:43.273
Yeah. yeah. I know how much it was.

554
00:28:43.276 --> 00:28:45.396
How the fuck did you make that shot?

555
00:28:46.900 --> 00:28:48.900
Yo. your game is on today.

556
00:28:48.902 --> 00:28:50.735
I've been thinking about this shit.

557
00:28:50.737 --> 00:28:52.362
How did you and Ghost get close enough

558
00:28:52.364 --> 00:28:54.616
to Diego Jimenez to pull that trigger?

559
00:28:55.237 --> 00:28:58.409
From what I can come up
with. Dre wanted Diego dead.

560
00:28:58.411 --> 00:29:00.956
- Ghost made a deal.
- With Dre?

561
00:29:01.706 --> 00:29:03.122
Why the fuck would he do that?

562
00:29:03.124 --> 00:29:04.526
Why is not the question.

563
00:29:04.529 --> 00:29:05.787
What you should be asking yourself is.

564
00:29:05.789 --> 00:29:07.877
what's Dre's side of the deal?

565
00:29:07.879 --> 00:29:11.256
Who's supposed to get dead? Me. you?

566
00:29:14.636 --> 00:29:16.675
- What up. fellas?
- What's up. Ghost?

567
00:29:16.678 --> 00:29:18.388
Tommy. I need to rap
with you for a minute.

568
00:29:18.390 --> 00:29:19.889
K. you mind if we have the room?

569
00:29:19.891 --> 00:29:21.057
You always send a motherfucker

570
00:29:21.059 --> 00:29:22.776
out the room like a goddamn kid.

571
00:29:22.779 --> 00:29:25.180
Like you forget who taught you
the game in the first place.

572
00:29:25.183 --> 00:29:27.230
Yo. K. you ain't got to go.

573
00:29:27.232 --> 00:29:28.573
I was headed out anyway.

574
00:29:31.611 --> 00:29:32.862
Y'all play nice.

575
00:29:36.324 --> 00:29:37.409
Later. K.

576
00:29:38.410 --> 00:29:41.035
Did you know that
LaKeisha got a subpoena

577
00:29:41.037 --> 00:29:42.662
to appear in front of a grand jury?

578
00:29:42.664 --> 00:29:45.415
- Shit.
- You're goddamn right. shit.

579
00:29:45.417 --> 00:29:48.126
She got to go under oath. and lie about

580
00:29:48.128 --> 00:29:51.296
where 'Riq and Tasha were
the night Ray Ray got shot.

581
00:29:51.298 --> 00:29:52.755
I think I got a plan. Tommy.

582
00:29:52.757 --> 00:29:54.507
It'll keep 'Keisha and all of us safe.

583
00:29:54.509 --> 00:29:55.842
Yeah. why don't that
make me feel better?

584
00:29:55.844 --> 00:29:57.135
Look. when I was on the inside.

585
00:29:57.137 --> 00:29:58.886
was Dre running product through Truth?

586
00:29:58.888 --> 00:30:00.513
Because I did the books. Tommy.

587
00:30:00.515 --> 00:30:01.808
He made too much money in there.

588
00:30:02.767 --> 00:30:04.894
- Yeah. that's how we did it.
- We?

589
00:30:04.897 --> 00:30:06.686
And you got an issue
with me keeping secrets?

590
00:30:06.688 --> 00:30:08.062
Come on. Tommy. do you understand

591
00:30:08.064 --> 00:30:09.478
how much you put at risk by doing that?

592
00:30:09.480 --> 00:30:11.608
Yeah. I do. my life.

593
00:30:11.610 --> 00:30:14.055
Milan kept us in it.
Petar said keep going.

594
00:30:14.058 --> 00:30:15.737
- I didn't have a choice.
- Okay. Tommy.

595
00:30:15.739 --> 00:30:17.488
I'll just use that. all right?

596
00:30:17.490 --> 00:30:20.158
I'll say I fired Dre for
running drugs through the club.

597
00:30:20.160 --> 00:30:21.973
Then he reached out to
his contact. Ray Ray.

598
00:30:21.976 --> 00:30:23.144
to get revenge on me.

599
00:30:23.147 --> 00:30:24.612
Of course. we've got to make sure

600
00:30:24.615 --> 00:30:26.705
that we keep his drug
dealing separate from ours.

601
00:30:26.708 --> 00:30:27.832
Then when we kill that nigga.

602
00:30:27.834 --> 00:30:29.459
we just drop a La Arana card on him.

603
00:30:29.461 --> 00:30:31.294
Yo. I got one better.

604
00:30:31.296 --> 00:30:33.630
We still got Diego's head. right?

605
00:30:33.632 --> 00:30:36.299
We drop that shit in Dre's place.

606
00:30:36.301 --> 00:30:38.675
that gives the Jimenez motive.

607
00:30:38.678 --> 00:30:40.219
That's better. and then we drop

608
00:30:40.221 --> 00:30:41.596
the murder weapon on him. too.

609
00:30:41.598 --> 00:30:43.306
Wait. what the fuck murder weapon?

610
00:30:43.308 --> 00:30:44.680
Tasha said she got rid of the gun.

611
00:30:44.683 --> 00:30:46.559
She told me the same shit.

612
00:30:46.561 --> 00:30:48.188
I'll explain later. all right?

613
00:30:50.105 --> 00:30:51.938
I ain't usually ride dirty like this.

614
00:30:51.941 --> 00:30:54.776
not since I got caught.
thanks to your mom and pop.

615
00:30:54.778 --> 00:30:56.778
I'm a little short on
manpower these days.

616
00:30:56.781 --> 00:30:57.996
Pfft. don't worry about it.

617
00:30:57.999 --> 00:30:59.821
Ghost gonna get his
time sooner or later.

618
00:30:59.824 --> 00:31:01.574
You going to fuck Ghost up?

619
00:31:01.576 --> 00:31:04.410
No. Ghost going to fuck himself up.

620
00:31:04.412 --> 00:31:06.287
He thinking about taking the rap for me

621
00:31:06.289 --> 00:31:08.706
on this whole Ray Ray shit.

622
00:31:08.708 --> 00:31:11.292
I ain't never know Ghost to
roll over like no little bitch.

623
00:31:11.294 --> 00:31:13.628
Motherfucker win. no matter what.

624
00:31:13.630 --> 00:31:15.588
You don't believe that
shit. though. right?

625
00:31:15.590 --> 00:31:18.468
I mean. I don't know. He
seemed real enough about it.

626
00:31:19.302 --> 00:31:21.969
I think he might try to
pin all of it on Dre first.

627
00:31:21.971 --> 00:31:26.015
Now. that do sound like Ghost.
Maybe you can trust that nigga.

628
00:31:26.017 --> 00:31:27.433
Close the trunk.

629
00:31:27.435 --> 00:31:29.185
Let's take this shit
to the "Eye-talians."

630
00:31:29.187 --> 00:31:30.980
and then I want to show you something.

631
00:31:51.960 --> 00:31:54.045
Don't you already have
everything you wanted?

632
00:31:54.879 --> 00:31:56.879
Relax. I'm gonna do you a favor.

633
00:31:56.881 --> 00:31:58.798
Oh. you're gonna do me a favor. really?

634
00:31:58.800 --> 00:32:00.675
After blackmailing me?

635
00:32:00.677 --> 00:32:02.456
That just means we're on the same side.

636
00:32:03.263 --> 00:32:06.690
My advice is that you
distance yourself from Andre.

637
00:32:06.693 --> 00:32:10.267
If you don't. you
won't win the election.

638
00:32:10.270 --> 00:32:13.523
I'm going to need more than
your word. and your spite.

639
00:32:20.655 --> 00:32:21.781
Here's the truth.

640
00:32:22.824 --> 00:32:24.075
I fired Andre.

641
00:32:25.034 --> 00:32:27.452
Because while I was
wrongfully imprisoned.

642
00:32:27.454 --> 00:32:30.455
I suspected he was pushing
drugs through this club.

643
00:32:30.457 --> 00:32:33.666
I was right. and ever
since. your friend. Andre.

644
00:32:33.668 --> 00:32:35.336
has had a vendetta against me.

645
00:32:36.212 --> 00:32:38.087
Why are you telling me this shit now?

646
00:32:38.089 --> 00:32:39.464
Because he's pulling the same tricks

647
00:32:39.466 --> 00:32:40.923
with the Basset Hotel Group.

648
00:32:40.925 --> 00:32:42.884
I can tell because of how
much money they've made

649
00:32:42.886 --> 00:32:44.677
in such a short amount of time.

650
00:32:44.679 --> 00:32:46.721
He's in with some bad people.

651
00:32:46.723 --> 00:32:49.015
and it's going to come
down on him real soon.

652
00:32:49.017 --> 00:32:51.350
which means that if you
don't break ties with him.

653
00:32:51.352 --> 00:32:53.229
he's gonna drag you to the bottom.

654
00:32:55.148 --> 00:32:56.524
What about you. James?

655
00:32:58.401 --> 00:32:59.861
You stick close to me.

656
00:33:00.612 --> 00:33:03.072
And I'll be pulling you
up with me to the top.

657
00:33:08.535 --> 00:33:11.870
Back in the day. me. Tommy. and
your pops used to run this block.

658
00:33:11.873 --> 00:33:14.123
We was around your age.
we was selling crack

659
00:33:14.125 --> 00:33:16.334
a hundred miles an hour up the street.

660
00:33:16.336 --> 00:33:18.338
Until the cops started
to know our faces.

661
00:33:19.088 --> 00:33:21.105
Every time they seen
us. they used to hop out.

662
00:33:21.108 --> 00:33:22.234
run down on us.

663
00:33:23.176 --> 00:33:25.804
Ghost would be gone before we
could even think to run and shit.

664
00:33:27.764 --> 00:33:29.933
See. he-he ain't try to outrun the cops.

665
00:33:30.683 --> 00:33:34.101
He just figured that as long
as he could outrun me and Tommy.

666
00:33:34.103 --> 00:33:35.812
the cops would settle for us.

667
00:33:35.814 --> 00:33:38.233
Nigga always thinking about himself.

668
00:33:39.901 --> 00:33:41.402
Well. it's worked for him so far.

669
00:33:45.490 --> 00:33:48.825
Take these dimes. hit
me when you get them off.

670
00:33:48.827 --> 00:33:50.440
When I get them off?

671
00:33:50.443 --> 00:33:52.286
How the fuck I'm supposed to do that?

672
00:33:52.288 --> 00:33:54.288
- I don't know these people.
- Figure it out.

673
00:33:54.290 --> 00:33:55.628
Don't come back until you do.

674
00:33:56.751 --> 00:33:58.543
Just don't get caught.

675
00:33:58.545 --> 00:33:59.546
All right.

676
00:34:06.553 --> 00:34:08.763
- Hey.
- Congratulations.

677
00:34:09.681 --> 00:34:10.972
Got your law license back.

678
00:34:10.974 --> 00:34:13.017
Ha. appreciate it.

679
00:34:14.978 --> 00:34:18.479
So. hey. uh. yeah. I was
going through old files.

680
00:34:18.481 --> 00:34:21.023
trying to get back up to speed. and...

681
00:34:21.025 --> 00:34:24.445
You know that guard at the MCC
who was giving you a hard time?

682
00:34:26.573 --> 00:34:29.075
Well. he was brutally murdered.

683
00:34:31.703 --> 00:34:34.401
You don't know anything
about that. right?

684
00:34:36.291 --> 00:34:39.250
Good. that's good.

685
00:34:39.252 --> 00:34:41.002
In-in not knowing anything about that.

686
00:34:41.004 --> 00:34:43.840
because I wasn't your
counsel at the time.

687
00:34:47.051 --> 00:34:50.138
There wouldn't have been
any witnesses. would there?

688
00:34:54.517 --> 00:34:56.144
So there's potential exposure?

689
00:34:58.688 --> 00:35:00.938
Could be. Did something happen. Joe?

690
00:35:00.940 --> 00:35:04.108
No. no. I am just doing my job.

691
00:35:04.110 --> 00:35:05.985
which is watching your back.

692
00:35:05.987 --> 00:35:07.322
Well. I appreciate that.

693
00:35:08.072 --> 00:35:09.574
But I do have a question for you.

694
00:35:12.619 --> 00:35:15.369
Let's say I decide to take the rap

695
00:35:15.371 --> 00:35:16.996
for something I didn't do.

696
00:35:16.998 --> 00:35:18.917
What's the collateral damage?

697
00:35:20.293 --> 00:35:22.921
- Care to be more specific?
- I can't be.

698
00:35:26.758 --> 00:35:30.259
Hypothetically. if you turn
yourself in for something.

699
00:35:30.261 --> 00:35:33.054
there is no way the State
is not gonna use that

700
00:35:33.056 --> 00:35:35.473
as an excuse to dig
deeper into your life.

701
00:35:35.475 --> 00:35:38.353
And you already got a big
target on your back. buddy.

702
00:35:40.521 --> 00:35:43.232
And what about the others
who are close to me?

703
00:35:44.442 --> 00:35:48.198
Is this what you were talking
about with Angela and Tasha?

704
00:35:48.201 --> 00:35:50.070
You know what. forget I asked about it.

705
00:35:50.073 --> 00:35:51.197
- No.
- Stupid idea.

706
00:35:51.199 --> 00:35:54.700
James. come on. You can trust me. okay?

707
00:35:54.702 --> 00:35:56.162
I'm watching your back.

708
00:35:56.955 --> 00:35:58.454
The more you tell me.

709
00:35:58.456 --> 00:36:00.708
that's the better I can advise you.

710
00:36:02.502 --> 00:36:04.712
Now. come on. James. you... Let me in.

711
00:36:08.549 --> 00:36:09.592
Thanks. Joe.

712
00:36:11.970 --> 00:36:13.221
Good seeing you.

713
00:36:18.184 --> 00:36:20.603
And then. this guy knocked on
my door and handed this to me.

714
00:36:22.105 --> 00:36:23.479
I'm being asked to appear

715
00:36:23.481 --> 00:36:25.274
on the witness stand in a grand jury.

716
00:36:27.276 --> 00:36:28.861
This is about you and Tariq. right?

717
00:36:29.529 --> 00:36:31.570
No. it's about Ghost.

718
00:36:31.572 --> 00:36:34.240
They think he murdered
the man who killed Raina.

719
00:36:34.242 --> 00:36:37.284
- Did he?
- No. he didn't.

720
00:36:37.286 --> 00:36:39.578
But the man who did is still out there.

721
00:36:39.580 --> 00:36:41.247
and the police aren't going after him.

722
00:36:41.249 --> 00:36:42.727
They're coming after us.

723
00:36:42.730 --> 00:36:45.064
What's your man. Silver.
saying about all this?

724
00:36:45.067 --> 00:36:47.820
- How can he help?
- He can't.

725
00:36:50.425 --> 00:36:52.216
You know the alibi I asked you for?

726
00:36:52.218 --> 00:36:54.802
- For me. Ghost. Tariq...
- Tommy.

727
00:36:54.804 --> 00:36:55.886
Yes.

728
00:36:57.807 --> 00:36:59.473
Well. I need one more.

729
00:36:59.475 --> 00:37:02.228
It's for the person who
we think killed Ray Ray.

730
00:37:05.064 --> 00:37:06.190
Hold up. Tash.

731
00:37:07.442 --> 00:37:11.070
So you're saying you know who
killed Raina's killer. right?

732
00:37:12.321 --> 00:37:14.780
But you're not gonna go to
the cops and tell them that.

733
00:37:14.782 --> 00:37:17.199
You want me to get on the witness stand.

734
00:37:17.201 --> 00:37:19.452
and risk my freedom and my life.

735
00:37:19.454 --> 00:37:20.619
to lie for you instead?

736
00:37:20.621 --> 00:37:21.912
'Keisha. I got you.

737
00:37:21.914 --> 00:37:23.531
You know I would never let that happen.

738
00:37:23.534 --> 00:37:24.999
How is it that you got me?

739
00:37:25.001 --> 00:37:27.418
Have I ever asked you to commit perjury?

740
00:37:27.421 --> 00:37:30.565
Have I ever hijacked your
business to clean drug money?

741
00:37:30.568 --> 00:37:32.548
Even on a basic level. Tash.

742
00:37:32.550 --> 00:37:34.467
Yas been over here a million times.

743
00:37:34.469 --> 00:37:36.763
When's the last time
you laid eyes on Cash?

744
00:37:40.308 --> 00:37:41.601
You know what. you're right.

745
00:37:44.312 --> 00:37:46.647
I admit it. I haven't
been a very good friend.

746
00:37:48.858 --> 00:37:51.569
But I have kept all of my promises.

747
00:37:54.865 --> 00:37:56.906
You know what. if you don't
want to do this for me.

748
00:37:56.908 --> 00:37:58.201
you can just say no.

749
00:37:59.077 --> 00:38:00.826
Lying about the amount of time

750
00:38:00.828 --> 00:38:02.622
y'all was at the penthouse is one thing.

751
00:38:05.208 --> 00:38:07.877
But me lying on somebody
who wasn't even there?

752
00:38:08.753 --> 00:38:12.639
That's something different.
That's a bold-faced lie.

753
00:38:12.642 --> 00:38:14.924
Tommy wasn't there. either.
but you could do it for him.

754
00:38:20.932 --> 00:38:22.850
I can't get justice for Raina.

755
00:38:24.477 --> 00:38:27.959
And I can't protect my family
